# 🧑‍💻 GPUI Component Code Implementations — Full Single-Binary Stack

All UI in GPUI starts with a view. Views build a tree of elements, lay them out and style them with a tailwind-style API, and then give them to GPUI to turn into pixels. Elements are the building blocks of UI in GPUI — they provide a wrapper around an imperative API that provides as much flexibility and control as you need. Elements have total control over how they and their child elements are rendered.

The core pattern is: **decode/render content → RGBA bitmap → display via GPUI `img()` element**.

